description:
Contains Bayesian implementations of Mixed-Effects Accelerated Failure Time (MEAFT) models
for censored data. Those can be not only right-censored but also interval-censored,
doubly-interval-censored or misclassified interval-censored.

Using piecewise constant hazards models is a very flexible approach
for the analysis of survival data. The time line is divided into sub-intervals;
for each interval, a different hazard is estimated using Poisson regression.

